Day 8 — Artifactory as Docker Registry
Why Use Artifactory as Your Docker Registry?
Single registry for all images (your own + proxied external)
Security scanning via Xray on every push/pull
Access control — who can push/pull which images
Immutability — production images can be locked
Replication — sync images between data centers
Build traceability — link image to its source build
Registry URL Structure

{server-name}.jfrog.io/{repo-name}/{image-name}:{tag}

mycompany.jfrog.io/docker-prod-local/myservice:1.0.0

Docker Repository Types
Local — your own images
Remote — proxy to Docker Hub, gcr.io, quay.io, etc.
Virtual — aggregates local + remote; single URL for all docker pulls
Docker Content Trust
Artifactory supports notary-based signing. Images can be signed and Xray can verify signatures — ensures image integrity from build to deployment.

Multi-architecture Images (OCI)
Artifactory stores OCI manifests and image indexes for multi-architecture images (amd64, arm64). A single pull URL works regardless of the target architecture.

